@page "/privacy-policy"

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy</PageTitle>

<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="Read this privacy policy to learn how data is collected, processed, protected, and managed." />
</HeadContent>

<div class="page-container page-section flow-lg">
    <div class="flow-sm">
        <div class="row text-primary">
            <AppIcon Name="lock" Class="icon-lg" />
            <h1 class="text-page-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
        </div>
        <p class="text-body text-muted">Last Updated: February 2026</p>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <section>
        <h2 class="text-section-title">1. Scope and Purpose</h2>
        <p class="text-body">
            This Privacy Policy explains how personal data is collected, used, stored,
            and protected when using this website and related services.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body">
            By accessing or using this website, users acknowledge the practices described
            in this policy.
        </p>
    </section>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <section>
        <h2 class="text-section-title">2. Information That May Be Collected</h2>
        <p class="text-body">
            Depending on usage, the following categories of information may be collected:
            technical data (for example IP address, browser type, device type, and pages visited),
            usage analytics, and information voluntarily submitted through contact forms or email.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body">
            Sensitive personal data is not intentionally requested unless explicitly required for
            a specific service.
        </p>
    </section>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <section>
        <h2 class="text-section-title">3. How Information Is Used</h2>
        <p class="text-body">
            Collected information may be used to operate and improve the website, maintain service
            performance and security, understand usage trends, respond to inquiries, and comply with
            legal obligations.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body">
            Information is processed only for legitimate purposes and is not sold to third parties.
        </p>
    </section>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <section>
        <h2 class="text-section-title">4. Analytics, Cookies, and Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p class="text-body">
            This website may use cookies or similar technologies for functionality, security,
            and analytics. Analytics providers or infrastructure partners may process limited
            technical data according to their own privacy terms.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body">
            Users can manage or disable cookies through browser settings. Disabling cookies may
            affect certain website features.
        </p>
    </section>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <section>
        <h2 class="text-section-title">5. Data Retention and Security</h2>
        <p class="text-body">
            Data is retained only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes described in
            this policy or to meet legal requirements.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body">
            Reasonable technical and organizational safeguards are applied to protect data.
            However, no internet transmission or storage system can be guaranteed to be fully secure.
        </p>
    </section>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <section>
        <h2 class="text-section-title">6. User Rights and Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-body">
            Subject to applicable laws, users may have rights to access, correct, delete,
            or restrict processing of their personal data. To submit a privacy-related request,
            use the contact channel below.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body"><strong>Contact Email:</strong> <a class="link-muted" href="mailto:contact@sametcc.me">contact@sametcc.me</a></p>
        <p class="text-caption text-muted">
            This policy may be updated from time to time. Continued use of the website after
            changes are published constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
        </p>
    </section>
</div>
